# color_ramp


# color ramp
ramp := a series of colors that transition, generally in brightness or luminousity

straight ramp := a ramp where only lighntess changes, like a monochromatic paletter with no hue shifting. Rarely used

# luminosity ramp
luminosity ramp := where brightness is replaced by percieved brightness.

see [luminosity_of_color](luminosity_of_color___20250304_1559_49.pd)

An increase in red is much more noticable than an increase in blue. There is an associated set of colors.

